Flanker: a tool for comparative genomics of gene flanking regions

Will Matlock and Sam Lipworth

26/01/2021

This R markdown script accompanies the manuscript Flanker: a tool for comparative genomics of gene flanking regions (Matlock/Lipworth et al 2021). Work through the code chunks sequentially or you can knit it. Any issues/questions please email samuel.lipworth@ndm.ox.ac.uk (wrote this R code) or william.matlock@wadham.ox.ac.uk / twitter @samlipworth @wtmatlock

Essentially we do three things: 1) take flanker output and classify Flank Patterns (Overall pattern over all window clusters) 2) plot a mashtree of plasmid assemblies 3) plot an schematic alignment of genes using gggenes

We then slot all these together in a facet plot and add some info on presence/absence of plasmids as called by Plasmidfinder.

This should be generally useful for anyone wanting to take Prokka output and plot an alignment against a tree.

Here we took a single representative member of each flank pattern (FP) and sketched these using Mash (on default settings). We then performed a mash screen against assemblies of all EUSCAPE isolates and assigned these to the top hit - e.g.mash screen FPs.msh file.fasta | sort -gk1 | tail -1
